<div class="mb-requirement-container">
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14148">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> </span>
      <b>NOTE: </b> The official merit badge pamphlets are now free and
      downloadable
      <a
        href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Pamphlets/Pulp-Paper.pdf"
        target="_blank"
        >HERE</a
      >
      or can be purchased at the
      <a href="https://www.scoutshop.org/" target="_blank ">Scout Shop.</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-5284">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 1. </span>
      Tell the history of papermaking. Describe the part paper products play in
      our society and economy. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/gvdeiWWOG8w" target="_blank"
        >The History of Paper From Ancient China to Modern Times (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-5291">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 2. </span>
      Learn about the pulp and paper industry.
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-5291 mb-requirement-id-5292">
        (a) Describe the ways the industry plants, grows, and harvests trees.
        <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/qNX5EkbqYek" target="_blank"
          >How They Grow Trees for Paper Manufacture (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-5291 mb-requirement-id-5293">
        (b) Explain how the industry manages its forests so that the supply of
        trees keeps pace with the demand. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/jGvlrhivWo8" target="_blank"
          >Forest Management (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-5291 mb-requirement-id-5294">
        (c) Tell how the industry has incorporated the concepts of sustainable
        forest management (SFM). <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/dYFt-3LNNNg" target="_blank"
          >Sustainable Forestry (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-5291 mb-requirement-id-5295">
        (d) Describe two ways the papermaking industry has addressed pollution.
        <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/bNjp_J3yang" target="_blank"
          >Green Spotlight on the Paper Industry (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-5296">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 3. </span>
      Name at least four types of trees that are major sources of papermaking
      fibers. Then do the following: <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a href="https://youtube.com/shorts/oRgPQdX0CLI" target="_blank"
        >What Kind of Tree Does Paper Come From (video)</a
      >
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-5296 mb-requirement-id-5297">
        (a) Discuss what other uses are made of the trees and the forestland
        owned by the pulp and paper industry. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.britannica.com/science/forestry/Range-and-forage"
          target="_blank"
          >Purposes and Techniques of Forest Management (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-5296 mb-requirement-id-5298">
        (b) Describe two ways of getting fibers from wood, and explain the major
        differences between them. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtube.com/shorts/c-87Bw_lXso" target="_blank"
          >From Tree to Paper (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-5296 mb-requirement-id-5299">
        (c) Tell why some pulps are bleached, and describe the process. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/d43q0j831f8" target="_blank"
          >Bleaching (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-5287">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 4. </span>
      Describe how paper is made. Discuss how paper is recycled. Make a sheet of
      paper by hand. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/OEbf9ffkyy8" target="_blank"
        >Production of Paper (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/invUjqvE0Oc" target="_blank"
        >From Tree to Sheet: How Paper Is Made | Unveiling the Manufacturing
        Process (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/Ow5LeG-zzyg" target="_blank"
        >How to Make Handmade Paper from Recycled Materials (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-5288">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 5. </span>
      Explain what coated paper is and why it is coated. Describe the major uses
      for different kinds of coated papers. Describe one other way that paper is
      changed by chemical or mechanical means to make new uses possible.
      <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/TCFpE6vtC4s" target="_blank"
        >Coated vs. Uncoated Paper (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-5289">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 6. </span>
      Make a list of 15 pulp or paper products found in your home. Share
      examples of 10 such products with your counselor.
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-5278">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 7. </span>
      With your parent or guardian's and counselor's approval, do ONE of the
      following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-5278 mb-requirement-id-5279">
        (a) Visit a pulp mill. Describe how the mill converts wood to cellulose
        fibers. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.afandpa.org/news/2025/how-paper-made-today"
          target="_blank"
          >How Is Paper Made Today? (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-5278 mb-requirement-id-5280">
        (b) Visit a paper mill and get a sample of the paper made there.
        Describe the processes used for making this paper. Tell how it will be
        used.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-5278 mb-requirement-id-5281">
        (c) Visit a container plant or box plant. Describe how the plant's
        products are made. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://corrugatedboxcompanies.com/more-corrugated-box-companies-listings/"
          target="_blank"
          >Corrugated Box Companies Listings (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-5278 mb-requirement-id-5282">
        (d) Visit a recycled paper collection or sorting facility. Describe the
        operations there. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/xEdwIHtK_6k" target="_blank"
          >Discover How Paper is Sorted for Recycling! (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/ZuZJZccjI34" target="_blank"
          >How Is Paper Recycled? (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://recycling-centers.regionaldirectory.us/"
          target="_blank"
          >Recycling Centers in the US (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-5278 mb-requirement-id-5283">
        (e) Using books, magazines, your local library, the internet (with your
        parent or guardian's permission), and any other suitable research tool,
        find out how paper products are developed. Find out what role research
        and development play in the papermaking industry. Share what you learned
        with your counselor. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/xcrVyh7s6zA" target="_blank"
          >Revolutionizing the Paper Industry (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://www.startus-insights.com/innovators-guide/pulp-and-paper-trends/"
          target="_blank"
          >Top 10 Pulp and Paper Trends &amp; Innovations in 2025 (website)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-5290">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 8. </span>
      Find out about three career opportunities in the papermaking industry that
      interest you. Pick one and find out the education, training, and
      experience required for this profession. Discuss this with your counselor,
      and explain why this profession might interest you. <br /><i
        >Resources:</i
      >
      <a href="https://youtu.be/JceCMm-kbg4" target="_blank"
        >Why a Career in Pulp and Paper Pays Off (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/QUeAwmqD4CM" target="_blank"
        >Career Opportunities at Catalyst Paper (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/yfZzS3zmytQ" target="_blank"
        >Amazing Summer Internships for Students at Pulp and Paper (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/-zw1BXofRK4" target="_blank"
        >Working for International Paper (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a
        href="https://www.indeed.com/career-advice/finding-a-job/jobs-in-paper-industry"
        target="_blank"
        >Jobs in the Paper Industry (website)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
